This course begins with a definition of public health and a review of its history and its role in disease prevention. 
The basic tools of public health practice, vital statistics and epidemiology, are then presented. 
The course concludes with an assessment of a health status of a community with the help of these tools.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing an introduction to public health principles and practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will be expected  - to gain an understanding of the principles and approaches of public health and its application in practice - to know and understand  the main indicators of public health  and their trends - to obtain skills in analyzing and interpreting the indicators necessary to assess the public health situation - to apply the knowledge to provide the necessary recommendations to solve the public health problem
